03/03/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A Macedonian trade representation office formally opened in Kosovo Wednesday (2 March), during a visit by Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski.
At the ceremony, he said the office would boost bilateral economic co-operation and contacts.
He also stressed UNMIK's contribution to the project.
During meetings with UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen and Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj, Buckovski again called for speedy demarcation of the Macedonian-Kosovo border, reiterating that the process should be completed as soon as possible and not linked to Kosovo's status.
(Makfax, A1 TV, Macedonian government Web site, KosovaLive, Tanjug - 02/03/05)
